This morning I challenged my body to a run and thought I was filming a running video only to open my phone in horror to some ~unflattering~ photos of myself that pushed my thigh & stomach insecurities to the surface…
 “Ew… why do my thighs not look toned” - I caught myself saying in my mind. 
 I immediately reframed this thought to speak to myself how I would talk to a best friend and reminded myself how strong my body is and started hyping up my thighs for carrying me back home safely!
 If you’ve been struggling with body image and confidence and are trying to hate yourself into a body that you love, this is my reminder to check in with your self-talk.
 Put your hands on the part of your body that you are feeling insecure about and speak these words out loud: 
I LOVE ___ PART OF MY BODY.
 Repeat it over and over for the next few weeks. You may not believe it at first but over time your relationship to that part of your body will SHIFT.
 You can LOVE yourself into a body that you LOVE. 
 I’m in it with you! We got this <3
 ily xx cal 
 #bodypositivity #bodypositive #selflove #confidencejourney #healthylifestyle #wellnessjourney #balancedlifestyle #fitnessjourney

several weeks ago, I received 2 prophetic words about a new ministry and had absolutely no idea what they were about…

the SAME week I opened my dms to a “random” message from a girl I looked up to during my season of getting back into my relationship with God aka @thegracevalentine … she invited me to be a leader at her Purpose Retreat for girls in their college/post grad season.

Fast forward, it’s May 18, I wake up at the crack of dawn, hop on a flight to NC only to have my now friend but total stranger at the time @maryevaphoto come up to me on the plane & introduce herself, only to be in the same car as me heading down to the retreat campus and my assigned roomie at the hotel.

We became instant friends over our shared bond for surfing, Goth Babe and half-Colombian Boyf/husbands 😂 - this was the first moment of the trip where I saw God working bc I’d been praying for community and it was no coincidence that He put Mary on my plane. 

When I said ‘yes’ to being a leader, I had absolutely zero idea what that would entail, and I had never shared this part of my testimony in front of 100+ people or led a 45-min breakout session, but I knew that God was calling me to something bigger then I could ever imagine. Even though it was way out of my comfort zone, I took a leap of faith and said ‘yes’…

The amount of cool God encounters that went down that weekend were more than the fingers on my hands (I share the deets on my most recent @healthybuthumanpod podcast episode), and the beautiful souls I got the chance to connect with and were countless.

Thank you @thegracevalentine for being such an inspiration & putting on the Purpose Retreat 🫶 This weekend was such a pivotal moment for me and so many others. 

And for my gals reading this who are feeling called to get out of their comfort zone, this is your sign to pray + take that leap of faith! You can’t grow without discomfort. <3

Sending you the love today !! 
xx cal

I keep seeing fitness creators open up about how they feel the algo doesn’t push “average looking bodies” as much as it promotes “thinspo” (similar to tumblr vibes).
 Last winter, I was struggling with an ED. As my weight dropped at an unhealthy pace, I noticed a huge spike in my views on socials. I didn’t think much of it until I noticed a correlation with my views and my body during the healing process/weight gain that followed.
 But lately, with more and more creators coming out on this topic, I’m starting to think I was actually on to something and not overthinking it… whether or not this is true or just a theory, I wanted to remind you that no matter what social media pushes at you, you are BEAUTIFUL AND ENOUGH just the way you are, my friend. 
 I know how hard it can feel when you see someone’s seemingly perfect photo online during a period of struggling with bad body image. I’ve been there too.
 Something that has helped me navigate body image and confidence (especially during the summer) is reading Psalms 139: 13-14 “For you created my inmost being; you knit me together in my mother’s womb. I praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made; your works are wonderful, I know that full well.”
 You are God’s beautiful masterpiece. He designed you. You are His creation.  Never ever let social media or anyone make you think otherwise.  Sending you sm love my queen!
 xx Cal
 #bodyimagehealing #confidence #healthylifestyle2023 #mentalhealthjourney #fitnessmotivation #selflovejourney

You don’t have to spend $400/month to be a reformer pilates girlie, here’s how 👇

March 2020, I officially became a certified Pilates instructor for a reformer studio in Miami, only to have my in-person teaching dreams put on hold as the fitness world shifted to online…

I’d been teaching barre classes at a local studio and had prior experience with mat work, so I got scheduled to lead virtual reformer inspired classes to help my clients “mimic” the reformer with sliders, resistance bands and weights.

After my first official reformer-inspired pilates class, I noticed my body felt the EXACT same during & after as a reformer class. Yes, there are exercises that simply cannot be done on the mat Vs reformer but overall, with the right form, it’s pretty close to the reformer!

Fast forward to starting my own Pilates studio + app, @sweatystudio , I not only pair affirmations with feel-good Pilates movement but also help you get the SAME results from your mat as you would with a reformer through my ✨reformer inspired workouts✨

This is ur sign to get started today and become a reformer pilates girl 😇

I hit a breaking point several nights ago… I was back in my old toxic cycle of binge watching Netflix till midnight only to snooze my alarm 10x and skip my morning routine aka the time when I would fill my cup…

I was so over the cycle that I decided that loving myself was not snoozing my alarm. It was doing my mind more harm than good.

So I woke up at 5am and had a super long morning packed with all the things I know my mind + bod need to fill my cup so that I can give to others!

I’m not saying everyone needs to wake up at 5, but I am saying that sometimes “loving yourself” can look like pushing yourself out of your comfort zone and breaking out of cycles.

If you’ve been in a funk or cycle, I’m here to remind you that you can do it! You are STRONG!

Fave morning routine habits:
- hot tea 
- soaking in God’s presence
- morning devotional
- @sweatystudio Pilates 
- hot girl walk with my doggo
- coffee shop (my stuart girlies check out @googancoffee )
- savory breakfast
- ACV drink to balance glucose 
- seed cycling 
- ocean swims

ily xx Cal

I had a full blown cry sesh over my body in these photos & wanted to remind you what I told myself to get out of my self-hatred moment…

Your body is designed to be a one of a kind you. Every day looks different and our bodies are always fluctuating. Just because an old version of you weighed less or fit a smaller size doesn’t mean that the current you is any less beautiful or worthy

Think about it like this - what if our society glorified the opposite of “skinny”? Would you want your body to look that way and do everything in your power to make it fit that mold? My answer was ya probably… 

The world will always try and tell us something is wrong about how we look and that we need to change to be loved, but that’s a LIE! Start to identify the lies in your mind and prove them wrong

ily xx cal

the BEST healthy brookie recipe 🍪👇

BROWNIE LAYER:
1/3 cup melted butter (or coconut oil if DF)
1/2 cup peanut butter
1 egg
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/3 cup coconut sugar
1 cup flour 
1/3 cup unsweetened cocoa powder 
1/2 tsp baking soda 
1/4 cup milk (I used @willas_kitchen choco oat milk)

COOKIE LAYER:
1/3 cup melted butter (or coconut oil)
1/3 coconut sugar 
3/4 cup flour
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2-3/4 cup of choco chips (I used dark chocolate)
1 egg
1 tsp vanilla extract

*oven at 350 degrees* 

1. Grab your brownie pan and spray with nonstick or use parchment paper/foil
2. Start with the brownie layer, slowly adding in the ingredients and blending
3. Pour brownie layer into pan and flatten 
4. Mix together cookie layer
5. Add cookie layer to top of brownie layer 
6. Andddd bake for 25-30 min (mine took closer to 30 since my pan was smaller but adjust according to your pan size)

Recipe inspo from Kale Junkie🫶

Your BODY. Your MIND. Deserve to have YOU TIME each day! 

I know how busy and chaotic and overwhelming life can feel. Sometimes a 5 min workout feels impossible to squeeze in with the 50 million other things battling for our energy, but hear me out… without a FULL BATTERY you have less energy and love to give. 

What’s the 1 thing that makes you feel relaxed, confident, strong and a better version of you? 

For me, that’s my daily form of movement - whether I’m doing Pilates at @sweatystudio , lifting some weights at the gym or simply strutting my stuff in my hot girl walk, when I move, I feel ALIVE and EMPOWERED. 

I challenge you to MAKE TIME for the thing that helps you renew and restore! You deserve it my queen 👑

P.S. If movement helps you feel amazing, come try my empowering workouts @sweatystudio :) link in bio to get started!

That voice running through your mind telling you that you aren’t “good enough” anytime you see the ‘perfect girl’ on social media who looks like she has her life put together is LYING to you! 

If you only looked at the first photo in this set, you’d probably think that about me… but let me break it to you, we are ALL humans. We all have those unflattering angles, weird quirks, off days, mood swings, not so cute moments. 

So if you’ve been struggling with comparison, I’m here to PROVE to you that what you see online isn’t the full picture (in fact I’m not even at the beach rn I’m typing this sitting on my porch covered in paint from house renovations haha). 

Keep on doing you and know that you ARE good enough because God literally chose YOU to be on this planet at this exact moment in time. 

And He created you to be uniquely you. Just like sunsets, there are no humans exactly the same! We are all beautiful masterpieces that God painted. 🫶

ily keep being kind to yourself and give yourself some grace today 

xx cal

One of the best pieces of advice I ever heard is that you can’t hate yourself into a body that you love… 

I spent YEARS of my life obsessing over every inch of my body. I spent so much time in HS & college trying to eat “perfectly healthy” while doing the “most effective workout routine”

And yet, I still hated my body and struggled with comparison to the point of tears.

It would be a lie if I told you my relationship with my body is perfect but I’ve definitely healed a ton and recognize that my body is doing the best she can with what I give her!

When I feel super stressed and am not getting enough sleep or pushing myself through workouts that aren’t aligned with my energy and have mean thoughts racing through my mind, I feel the most lethargic and bloated. 

But when I choose to listen to my body’s energy and hormone levels and hype her up like a bestie, i see myself through a loving lens. 

You my queen are beautiful exactly where you are! Your size, shape, weight doesn’t define your value or worth. You are more than the physical and deserve to love yourself bc God made you YOU! 

ily and hope this helps you <3 xx cal

“Callie you need to lose weight if you want to compete” - my skating coach

My 17-year-old self heard, “Callie, you’re fat and will never be successful unless you’re skinny.” 

For YEARS I believed this lie and honestly some days it still runs through my mind when a workout reel doesn’t hit… 

This is 1 way the enemy tries to pull us away from God’s love, by convincing us that even though God made us in His Image, we’re still not pretty enough to be the next famous influencer, skinny enough to be desired by that guy or funny enough to have friends. 

The next time you look through your photos or in the mirror and fall into the negative self-talk trap, I challenge you to ask God to help you see yourself how He sees you. 

Give it a moment. Wait in the silence. And hold onto His voice - the voice that runs through your mind and brings you peace and clarity, not confusion and anxiety.

The best way to heal your body image is to break the lies you’ve been believing. Identify the root trigger where the lie first began. Ask Jesus to show you where He was in that moment and ask Him to show you what He thought of you then. 

Oh and btw what you see online is a total curated highlight reel (even photos like these I still took time to pick them out of 1000s).

ilysm you are beautiful & wonderfully made! 

xx Cal

I used to think my body didn’t deserve this…

This all changed when I learned that you can’t hate yourself into a body that you love and changed my mindset from “all or nothing” to 1% better each day 🤍 

1% better can mean spending time with your besties or taking a Pilates class or having a much needed rest day.

You DESERVE balance and DESERVE to be social and enjoy the holidays free of any guilt! 

If you struggle with food guilt, an affirmation that helps me a lot when I eat is “My body deserves this food and is getting nourished.”

1. bicycle variation - 15x per side

pro tip- keep your knees stacked over your hips so that your lower abs will get stronger by keeping you stable

2. hollow crunch (I promise it’s more fun than a normal crunch 😂 but like in a spicy way) - 15x

if you find your lower back is trying to arch on this move, lift your legs a lil’ higher as your extend them and work on “tucking” or pelvic tilt your hips under 

3. flutter kicks - 30x total 

same as above on the back arch top! another modification is to take a 3/4 bend in your legs :)

ily have fun and don’t forget to talk kindly to yourself bc your body is doing the best it can!

the ability to move is a BLESSING ❤️ 

1. Self-care - find a form of movement that you love and it will be that special time for you to get stronger while also having fun and feeling GOOD. You can create a cozy environment with dim lights, candles & comfy clothes if that’s your vibe or take it outside!

2. Gratitude - not everyone has the chance to move and it’s truly a blessing. This time can be a time filled with thanking God for giving you the opportunity to get stronger!

3. Therapy - feel good endorphins are a thing and sometimes you need a sweaty workout after that cry sesh to let it all out and get stronger mentally 

4. Worship - we can worship Jesus with our body, especially through movement! Maybe pop on some worship music, talk to Him through it all and lean on Him when it’s hard. This can be such a cool time for praising God. 

5. Love - movement is powerful bc when you move in an empowering way, you’re treating your body with love and like a bestie! Key point here is to find that workout you actually ENJOY! It does exist I promise!

BABY GUALY COMING SOON FALL’24 🍼💛😇

I’m 5 weeks ish pregnant & can’t wait to take you along the ENTIRE journey of my pregnancy instead of waiting till the first trimester is up!! 

This baby is already such a huge blessing. We weren’t totally sure if we were ready to be pregnant again after what happened in October but God’s hand has been in it all and He gave us such peace + joy about it…

Several weeks before I found out, a man came up to us at our church who had prayed for us with his wife the day after we lost our first baby, and told us that he had been praying for us and felt the Lord say that we need to buy a physical baby product to declare that we WILL be having a baby. The next day, my friend told me she had a vision of me holding a baby in a swaddle. And at this time, I had NO idea I was pregnant. 

Fast forward, John and I are driving to Texas for Christmas and I started feeling literally so so tired to the point where no matter how long I slept I still felt tired. I felt like this the first time around and started to wonder if maybe I could be pregnant… 

The day after we got home for our trip I was feeling so exhausted that I needed to know if I was pregnant or something else was going on 😂 so I took several tests and we have a baby!!!!!! 

I can’t wait to show you the realness of being pregnant, how I’m navigating that with running my Pilates studio and continuing to stay a healthy queen while loving my body during its changes.

I’ve been sleeping in a ton, trying to eat nourishing meals and moving my body to meet its energy and so far so good!
